properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 7 at 11:56AM PST until February 9 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Gusty Northerly and Easterly Winds Sunday...

.An area of low pressure will bring a period of gusty northerly
and easterly winds to the region on Sunday. The strongest winds
are expected on the west side of the Valley and into Lake County
and on higher elevations of the Sierra. Winds will begin to
weaken Sunday night into Monday morning.

* WHAT...Northerly and easterly winds 20 to 30 mph. Valley gusts
between 30 to 45 mph. Upper foothills and mountain gusts
between 30 and 60 mph, stronger gusts possible for the higher
elevations.

* WHERE...Northern Sacramento Valley, Central Sacramento Valley,
Southern Sacramento Valley, Carquinez Strait and Delta,
Northern San Joaquin Valley, Mountains Southwestern Shasta
County to Northern Lake County, Clear Lake/Southern Lake
County, Western Plumas County/Lassen Park and West Slope
Northern Sierra Nevada Counties.

* WHEN...From 10 AM to 10 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree
limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
Difficult driving conditions for small and high profile
vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Northeast winds may cause downed trees in
the Delta region due to the unusual wind direction. Strong
easterly winds could impact outdoor recreational activities on
the Sierra.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 10 PM PST SUNDAY
